               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-215" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-215" type="surname" value="SEWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-215" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>STEPHEN SEWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a tailor, and live in Fetter-lane. About two o'clock in the afternoon of the 12th of July I was called, and saw the prisoner and another in the shop—the other asked the price of a waistcoat—I said it was not one they could afford to buy—they went out—I turned, and missed a waistcoat and trowsers—I followed them out, stopped the pri<lb></lb>soner, and took these trowsers from under his left arm—I asked for the waistcoat—he denied having it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-216" type="witnessName">
